abstract: The goal of treatment is to show you this — not to make you feel more secure or comforted.
snippet: The goal of treatment is to show you this — not to make you feel more secure or comforted.
lead_paragraph: I’m a psychiatrist who has spent most of the past 30 years treating patients with moderate to severe mental illness. But I’ve also administered care for the Massachusetts Department of Mental Health, Harvard Medical School and several insurance companies, and so I’m often asked for advice by colleagues who feel their patients need more help than an insurer is willing to pay for. In addition to offering technical advice, I often become, in essence, the therapists’ therapist, at least in terms of their treatment choices. And sometimes those interactions are as intense as therapy itself.

abstract: For generations, confusion and uncertainty have surrounded the “natural born citizen” presidential requirement, and demand is mounting for an answer to the modern meaning.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After he left Wall Street to enter politics eight years ago, Representative Jim Himes, Democrat of Connecticut, began fielding the occasional question of when he intended to run for president.

abstract: The couple met in 2010 while working at the Jewish Community Center of Greater Washington.
snippet: The couple met in 2010 while working at the Jewish Community Center of Greater Washington.
lead_paragraph: Alison Brooke Gordon, the daughter of Glenda R. Gordon and Kenneth A. Gordon of Boca Raton, Fla., was married there Jan. 9 to Kyle Eugene Gugerty, the son of Francine A. Farber of Bethesda, Md., and Michael J. Gugerty of Rockville, Md. Rabbi Bennett Miller officiated at the Addison, an event space.

abstract: Confrontations between reality-based movies and a growing pack of watchdogs have been turning the Academy Awards ritual into a brutal game of “gotcha.”
snippet: Confrontations between reality-based movies and a growing pack of watchdogs have been turning the Academy Awards ritual into a brutal game of “gotcha.”
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — About 45 minutes into “The Big Short,” Adam McKay’s “true story” — or so it says on the billboards — of Wall Street greed, the actor Finn Wittrock turns to the camera and confesses, “O.K., so this part isn’t totally accurate.”

abstract: Seattle (10-6), a 5½-point favorite to win at Minnesota (11-5) on Sunday, has the potential to be a dangerous team in the N.F.L. playoffs.
snippet: Seattle (10-6), a 5½-point favorite to win at Minnesota (11-5) on Sunday, has the potential to be a dangerous team in the N.F.L. playoffs.
lead_paragraph: The Seahawks have finished the season as the sixth and lowest seed in the N.F.C. playoffs; they must travel to Minnesota for the first round, and will not get a home game no matter how far they advance.

abstract: President Obama is the first president to publish visitor logs of the journalists who attend off-the-record discussions meant to promote context and candor.
snippet: President Obama is the first president to publish visitor logs of the journalists who attend off-the-record discussions meant to promote context and candor.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Hours after President Obama announced in a 2014 speech that he was escalating his campaign against Islamic extremists, a number of prominent columnists suggested they knew exactly what he was thinking.
